    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen the window is first opened, everything works fine.\n\n<img width=\"572\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3db497b7-451a-4dda-86e5-bb2b4b2cb5ed\" />\n\nNow press `<C-s>` to cycle and the window height will be set to 1\n\n<img width=\"574\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4999dbde-5443-4023-a14e-40ea2b61bde4\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n-- init.lua\nvim.lsp.config['clangd'] = { cmd = { 'clangd' } }\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\n```\n\n```cpp\n// foo.cc\n#include <algorithm>\n\nint main()\n{\n  std::max(\n        // ^ put the cursor here\n        //    now press <C-s> 3 times in insert mode\n  return 0;\n}\n\n```\n\n```nvim --clean -u init.lua foo.cc```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe window should adapt to the specific content\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.4.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm2 3.5.13\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nGithub Release Page",
